<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910502-0121</DOCNO><DOCID>910502-0121.</DOCID><HL>   Letters to the Editor:   Family Tradition</HL><DATE>05/02/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A17</SO><LP>   David Shribman, in his April 11 Leisure andamp; Arts review of&quot;Three Men of the Beagle,&quot; asserts that Beagle Capt. RobertFitzRoy killed himself by &quot;slit{ting} his wrists.&quot; This isnot correct. FitzRoy committed suicide by cutting the carotidartery in his neck with a razor. The same method of suicidewas used by his uncle, British Foreign Secretary LordCastlereagh.   Ralph Colp Jr., M.D.</LP><TEXT>   New York</TEXT></DOC>